<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They have been presenting their Heart Breakfast radio show throughout the pandemic. </p>

<p>And Amanda Holden was looking effortlessly stylish in a fun green miniskirt as she strutted out of the Heart Radio studios on Tuesday.</p>

<p>The Britain's Got Talent judge, 49, put on a leggy display in the fun skirt as she left Global after hosting the early morning show. </p>

<p>Looking good: Amanda Holden, 49, looked effortlessly stylish in a fun green miniskirt as she strutted out of the Heart Radio studios on Tuesday</p>

<p>Amanda cut a chic figure in the thigh-skimming green skirt as she headed out of the studio.</p>

<p>She teamed the fun look with a stand-out 'disco' T-shirt and white heels which further highlighted her svelte physique.</p>

<p>Ahead of her radio show, Amanda and her co-presenter Ashley Roberts shared a fun video to Instagram as they strutted down the hallway at Global studios while flicking their hair. </p>

<p>Gorgeous: The Britain's Got Talent judge put on a leggy display in the fun skirt as she left Global after hosting the early morning show</p>

<p>Lovely: She teamed the fun look with a stand-out 'disco' T-shirt and white heels which further highlighted her svelte physique</p>

<p>Well-dressed: Amanda completed her look with a statement black handbag and cat-eye sunglasses</p>

<p>Amanda captioned the fun clip with 'because we're worth it' followed by a crying laughing emoji.</p>

<p>In the slow motion video, the two stars strutted down the hallway in sync as they sultrily flicked their blonde locks in time.</p>

<p>Amanda styled her blonde locks into a glossy blow-dried hairdo and added a slick of glamorous make-up.</p>

<p>Meanwhile Ashley looked effortlessly chic in a pair of white high-waisted trousers with an unbuttoned shirt tucked into them.</p>

<p>Fun times: Amanda also shared a glimpse of her latest presenting look with a fun Instagram snap on Tuesday </p>

<p>Work it: She also shared a hilarious video of herself and Ashley Roberts as they strutted down the hallway at Global studios while flicking their hair</p>

<p>Sensational: Amanda captioned the fun clip with 'because we're worth it' followed by a crying laughing emoji</p>

<p>It comes after Amanda made a dramatic entrance for the first Britain's Got Talent semi-final on Saturday.</p>

<p>The presenter slipped into a plunging gold metallic dress as she took her place on the socially-distanced judging panel </p>

<p>Amanda was in high spirits after being promoted to head judge for the semi-finals, as it was also revealed that her debut album Songs From My Heart had reached number one on the iTunes pre-order charts.  </p>

<p>In sync! In the slow motion video, the two stars strutted down the hallway in sync as they sultrily flicked their blonde locks in time</p>

<p>Stylish! Amanda looked sensational as she displayed her toned figure in a green mini skirt and 'disco' T-shirt</p>

<p>Due to Simon Cowell's absence Amanda has been promoted to head judge, and she was quick to joke she'll be backing 'musical theatre all the way.' </p>

<p>Simon was forced to pull out after breaking his back in a cycling accident, and after a six-hour operation has been recovering at home. </p>

<p>The music mogul has insisted producers have made the show the best it can be despite social distancing now being in place - and has even hinted he will indeed appear at the live final in October, despite being on bed rest.  </p>

